From 8f350860483f63b4339fea96c6873451f5c284e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Florian Fuchs <fuchsfl@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 21:22:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Input: maplecontrol - add missing input_sync()

dc_pad_callback() reports button and axis state on every poll but never
calls input_sync(), so no EV_SYN/SYN_REPORT is emitted. evdev only wakes
readers on SYN_REPORT, so events accumulate unseen until the buffer
overflows and flushes them in a burst.

The maplemouse and maple_keyb drivers already sync; add the missing call
to the joystick driver so each poll delivers a complete event packet.

Fixes: 01461d7e65a6 ("Input: add support for Maple controller as a joystick")
Signed-off-by: Florian Fuchs <fuchsfl@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/input/joystick/maplecontrol.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/input/joystick/maplecontrol.c b/drivers/input/joystick/maplecontrol.c
index 7f36f73844a9..2a4b73731ddd 100644
--- a/drivers/input/joystick/maplecontrol.c
+++ b/drivers/input/joystick/maplecontrol.c
@@ -58,6 +58,8 @@ static void dc_pad_callback(struct mapleq *mq)
 	input_report_abs(dev, ABS_Y,      res[13]);
 	input_report_abs(dev, ABS_RX,     res[14]);
 	input_report_abs(dev, ABS_RY,     res[15]);
+
+	input_sync(dev);
 }
 
 static int dc_pad_open(struct input_dev *dev)
